news.title: No nod to stilt plus four floor building plans in Haryana
news.para: The directorate ordered that no new stilt plus 4-storey construction plan will be approved till further orders. However, it was clarified that all such plans approved earlier will be valid.

news.title: We pay upkeep fee, why give parking charge too: Gaur City residents
news.para: According to the residents, instead of removing unauthorised parking, the builder is engaging in converting the spots into a money collection exercise.

news.title: Gurugram: Builder sells land to another, DTCP goes to cops for FIR
news.para: According to DTCP officials, KN Infracon Pvt Ltd submitted an application on June 15, 2020, for the migration of its 2010 licence granted for a group housing colony on 11.381 acres of land in Sector 106 into an affordable housing colony.

news.title: Licences of three affordable housing projects suspended in Gurugram
news.para: The licences were granted to Ocean Seven Buildtech Pvt Ltd in 2016, 2018 and 2019 to develop Expressway Towers in Sector 109, Golf Heights in Sector 69 and The Venetian in Sector 70, respectively.

news.title: Yes Bank-DHFL scam: Accused to be tried by PMLA court, says Bombay HC
news.para: Yes Bank cofounder, Rana Kapoor and erstwhile DHFL founders Kapil and Dheeraj Wadhawan have been arrested by both the CBI and the ED in the cases connected to the fraud caused to the private bank when Kapoor was at its helm.

news.title: SC seeks CBI reply on Piramal Capital and Housing Finance plea in DHFL case
news.para: In September 2021, PCHF had completed the acquisition of bankrupt DHFL for Rs 34,250 crore which includes a cash component and non-convertible debentures.

news.title: CBI recovers assets worth over Rs 50 crore during searches against directors of Gardenia India
news.para: The agency has registered a case against directors/guarantors Sanjeev Kumar, Manoj Kumar Ray, Anupama Kumari, Poonam Kumar, Gardenia India and corporate guarantors Gardenia Shelters and Futech Shelters, they said.

news.title: Sebi proposes changes to rules for REITs, InvITs
news.para: Coming out with a consultation paper on the subject, the markets regulator said the changes are being proposed keeping in mind the interest of unit holders and the structural vulnerabilities associated with absence of a sponsor for REITs and InvITs.

news.title: Telangana government to provide Rs 3,000 crore loan for metro to recover from loss
news.para: The government will immediately provide 1,000 crore and the rest will be given in a phased manner, sources said. L&THMRL has a debt burden of 13,000 crore.

news.title: Sun, sand and no inheritance tax fuel property boom in Mauritius
news.para: Interest has been robust, with more than 80% of all available units in final negotiations, the developer said in January. Only “a few units” with the four-bedroom configuration have yet to be sold.

news.title: Arkavathy layout scheme became a scam: Karnataka CM reads conclusion of Kempanna commission report
news.para: In the absence of former chief minister and opposition leader Siddaramaiah, who had set up the commission, Bommai took a swipe at the Congress and read the concluding portion of the commission report.

news.title: Noida-like township in Bundelkhand region could be a reality soon
news.para: While the idea is in its nascent stage, sources said the requisite initial budget required for the initiation of the ambitious project is likely to be drawn from the provisions for industrial development in the state budget 2023-2024.

news.title: Gujarat allocates Rs 1,066 crore to provide PMAY-Urban houses during next year
news.para: Gujarat finance minister Kanubhai Desai made a provision of Rs 932 crore for constructing houses under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana-Gramin (PMAY-G).

news.title: Land sale racket busted in Bhubaneswar
news.para: The EOW crackdown took place following a complaint lodged by Lipika Das of Khandagiri here on Tuesday. In her complaint, Das alleged that her 2,000 sqft vacant land at Malipada mouza in Khurda district was fraudulently sold to a man on October 21, 2020, without her knowledge.

news.title: In budget 2023-24, Haryana CM proposes to take up three more metro links
news.para: ​Khattar said that the long pending Gurugram Metro project has been approved by the Public Investment Board in the central government and the final approval of the Union Cabinet is awaited.
